title: Jin leads by 1 into final round of Asia-Pacific Amateur
text:
Jin leads by 1 into final round of Asia-Pacific Amateur By -   
HONG KONG (AP) - Jin Cheng of China pitched to a half-foot on the par-5 18th and made birdie for a 1-under 69 to take a one-stroke lead over two Australians after three rounds of the Asia-Pacific Amateur. 
Jin, who led after the opening two rounds, had a 54-hole total of 11-under 199 at Clearwater Bay. Australian amateur champion Cameron Davis and countryman Ryan Ruffels, the highest-ranked amateur in the field at No. 8, were one behind after 67s. 
Yu Chun-an (67) of Taiwan and South Korea’s Kim Tae-ho (69), were tied for fourth, three behind. Defending champion Antonio Murdaca of Australia shot 64 to move into sixth, four off the lead. 
Winds picked up late in the day, toppling a crane used for TV coverage, but there were no immediate reports of injuries.
